Upon update of OnDemand, a previously existing user created template for a space is no longer available to administer.  It should be displayed in: {code}https://<instance>/wiki/pages/templates2/listpagetemplates.action?key=<space-key>{code}

The template remains available for space usage and a constructed URL of the template appends the template under the 'Attachments' menu:
{code}https://<instance>/wiki/pages/templates2/viewpagetemplate.action?entityId=<template-id>&key=<space-key>{code}  

You can construct the edit URL to make changes:  {code}https://<instance>/wiki/pages/templates2/editpagetemplate.action?entityId=<template-id>&key=<space-key>{code}

The user is unable to recreate a template of the same name as it already exists in the database.

Although the [Creating PDF in another language|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Creating+PDF+in+Another+Language] documentation is still pointing users to the _https://<account_name>.atlassian.net/wiki/admin/flyingpdf/configurepdflanguagesupport.action_ URL, it isn't accessible to users without sysadmin rights anymore. The *PDF Export Language Support* menu option isn't visible for them either.

I understand that this isn't a new Restricted Function, but if it is, the documentation should be updated accordingly (both the [Restricted Functions List|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AOD/Restricted+Functions+in+Atlassian+OnDemand] and the [Creating PDF in another language|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Creating+PDF+in+Another+Language] how-to). Otherwise, the users should regain access to the functionality.

{panel}
h4. Update on this issue
Confluence Cloud administrators are not able to upload font collections directly, but you can request Atlassian Support to upload a collection for you. 

See our Confluence Cloud documentation for more information: [Create a PDF in another language|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFCLOUD/Create+a+PDF+in+Another+Language]{panel}

In a particular case reported by a customer, clicking the 'Create' button brought up a dialog with a infinite spinner, so they could not create any content. It turned out that the AJAX call to:
* {{/wiki/rest/create-dialog/1.0/blueprints/web-items?spaceKey=FOO}}

was failing with the following response:
{noformat}
{
    "errorCode": 500,
    "errorMessage": "Active Objects failed to initalize for bundle com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-feature-discovery-plugin",
    "errorType": "UNKNOWN"
}
{noformat}

However, all the health checks were passing (including the "Active Objects" and "Required Plugins" checks).

This plugin (confluence-feature-discovery-plugin) is already flagged as a required plugin in:
* https://stash.atlassian.com/projects/CONF/repos/confluence/browse/confluence-core/confluence/src/etc/java/com/atlassian/plugin/metadata/application-required-plugins.txt

So it appears the plugin itself is loading, but some Active Objects stuff that it needs to actually function is not.

I would expect at least one of the two aforementioned checks to fail, since a required plugin has not loaded properly and has broken critical application functionality.

h3. Summary
When inserting the 'Sprint Burndown Gadget’ in a Confluence page, the chart does not render correctly. Before it used to render the chart fully and on first load. 

h3. Environment
{{Confluence 5.9.1-OD-2015.45.1-0006}}

Chrome {{Version 46.0.2490.80 (64-bit)}}
Firefox {{42.0}}
Safari {{Version 9.0.1 (11601.2.7.2)}}


h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a sprint with issues that have story points
# In Confluence, create a page and insert the Sprint Burndown Gadget

h3. Expected Results
Insert macro and the chart renders correctly on first load. 


h3. Actual Results
Chart does not render correctly. Sometimes the chart is cut in half or does not load when first visiting the page. 

The following error is displayed in Chrome console
{noformat}
Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'renderReopenButton' of undefined
{noformat}

The following error is displayed in Firefox console
{noformat}
TypeError: h is undefined
{noformat}

The following error is displayed in Safari console
{noformat}
TypeError: undefined is not an object (evaluating 'h.renderReopenButton')
{noformat}
 

h3.Workaround
Click the cog > Refresh
